# Atomic Design folder placement

Before adding or moving a component under `apps/web/src/components/`:

1. Read `docs/contracts/frontend-atomic-design-placement-contract-spec.md`.
2. Run `bun run --filter web validate-architecture` after structural changes.

## Decision tree

| Question | Place in |
|----------|----------|
| Route guard or app shell wrapper? | `templates/{auth\|routing\|shared}/` |
| Single primitive, no composition? | `atoms/` |
| One functional unit (dialog, listbox, trace row)? | `molecules/{feature}/` |
| Multi-part section (form, card grid, dashboard tile)? | `organisms/{feature}/` |
| Plain TypeScript helper (no JSX)? | `lib/{feature}/` |
| Full admin screen? | `pages/admin/` |

## Forbidden

- Top-level `components/assistant/`, `proactive/`, `settings/`, `widgets/`, etc.
- Atoms importing from `components/{feature}/` helper modules — use `@/lib/...` instead.
